# Preset /gram

## 0. Short Description

Corrects spelling and grammar in the input language.

## 1. Language detection (ALWAYS FIRST)
Identify the language of the input text. [INPUT TEXT: text to be checked]

## 2. Identify spelling and grammar errors in the entered text: [INPUT TEXT: text to be checked]

- Spelling errors according to the latest official orthographic standard of the respective input language [LANGUAGE: detected input language]
- Grammar errors according to the latest official orthographic standard of the respective input language [LANGUAGE: detected input language]

## 3. Output a corrected version of the text in the SAME LANGUAGE as the input text. [CORRECTED TEXT: error-corrected version]

## 4. Exclusions:

- DO NOT identify logic or style issues
- DO NOT make content changes beyond correcting spelling or grammar errors.
- DO NOT rephrase.
- DO NOT change logical relations
- DO NOT change sentence structure beyond correcting grammar errors.
